trans-unit.note:
This setting is use the user drops or pastes image data into the editor. In this case, VS Code automatically creates a new image file in the workspace containing the dropped/pasted image. It's easier to explain this setting with an example. For example, let's say the setting value was:
{ 'docs/*.md': '${documentDirName}/images/${fileName}' }
Here the setting is an object mapping from a set of globs to a set of file destinations. The left hand side ('docs/*.md') is a glob that matches against a markdown document. If the glob, matches then we use the right hand side to compute the new file's path and name. The right hand side can also use the special variables document in this setting description.
